{{Quote|Dey gum up everyt'ing. 'Specially d'ventilators. D'rot'll eat t'rough d'best filters we got in a hour, mebbe less; y'got to change 'em every flight—you don't, d'Spore Sickness get into d'ship and get into you. Not a good way to go, b'lieve it, coughin' up blood 'n' cooking in y'own juices.|A Kubaz pilot, to Barriss Offee|<ref name="MBS">''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]''</ref>}}
'''Spore Sickness''' was a common term used to describe any number of illnesses that could be contracted by breathing in the adaptogenic spores of the multitude of fungi that were native to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Drongar/Legends|Drongar]]. The spore sickness was especially common among offworlders, who had not yet adjusted to Drongar's unique environment. For this reason, incoming [[Starship/Legends|starships]] regularly cleaned their ventilation systems before and after arriving at Drongar. In most cases, spore sickness caused damage to the lungs, forcing the body to battle the spores by raising the body temperature to exceptionally high levels, essentially cooking an individual in their own body fluids. However, the spores were only dangerous when encountered in the [[Atmosphere/Legends|atmosphere]]. At ground levels, the spores appeared to be harmless. Such diseases included [[spleen-rot]] and [[Ascomycetous pneumoconiosis]].

